This paper is about natural language processing and specifically about parsing Abstract Meaning Representation (AMR) from plain text. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses machine learning techniques, such as Stack-LSTMs, to make decisions, which suggests it could also fit into cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses improving results by adding additional information, such as POS tags and dependency trees, which could also place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
